Oyo State chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has advised candidates contesting for various elective positions to come with the original copies of their credentials. The party said that the screening was compulsory for aspirants vying for the National Assembly and House of Assembly seats. There are three senatorial districts and fourteen House of Representatives seats in Oyo State. The State also has 32 House of Assembly seats. The party enjoined all aspirants contesting for these seats to come with the original copies of their credentials for screening ahead of the forthcoming primary election. It made this announcement via a statement signed by Secretary of the party, Alhaji Wasiu Adeleke. The statement was made available to DAILY POST Tuesday evening. “This is to inform all our State Assembly and National Assembly Aspirants that there will be screening tomorrow at the State Secretariat, Molete, Ibadan. “For the purpose of emphasis, National Assembly and State Assembly Aspirants screening is tomorrow Wednesday 27th of April, 2022 at the State Secretariat, Molete, Ibadan “All Aspirants should come with the original copies of their necessary credentials. “The screening starts by 08am,” he said.